WEBVTT

00:00:42.799 --> 00:00:43.679
Your every move

00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:45.439
is exactly like Captain Jack.

00:00:47.320 --> 00:00:48.240
It seems your theory

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:49.520
is becoming more refined.

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:51.600
It's thanks to you that it's perfect.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:52.280
Come on.

00:00:52.679 --> 00:00:53.320
Let me defeat you

00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:54.520
to prove that I am right.

00:02:40.759 --> 00:02:41.719
I am right.

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:43.240
My theory is correct.

00:02:43.560 --> 00:02:44.319
According to my calculations,

00:02:44.639 --> 00:02:45.919
the probability of me winning this match

00:02:46.199 --> 00:02:48.000
has reached 99.7%.

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:48.479
You lose.

00:02:49.240 --> 00:02:50.240
You lose to mathematics.

00:02:50.680 --> 00:02:52.159
Are you that confident in your math?

00:02:52.159 --> 00:02:52.520
Yes.

00:02:52.960 --> 00:02:53.520
I told you.

00:02:53.879 --> 00:02:55.759
Everyone has a fixed playing pattern.

00:02:55.919 --> 00:02:57.120
Your shooting stance and strategy

00:02:57.240 --> 00:02:58.199
determine your shot trajectory.

00:02:58.240 --> 00:02:59.199
It can be calculated.

00:02:59.479 --> 00:02:59.840
So,

00:03:00.240 --> 00:03:01.199
as long as you are the one playing,

00:03:01.560 --> 00:03:03.439
my prediction of your shots won't be wrong.

00:03:08.719 --> 00:03:10.439
What if you were playing someone else?

00:03:11.759 --> 00:03:12.400
What?

00:03:12.759 --> 00:03:14.639
Six Divine Techniques - Blossoms in Disarray.

00:03:15.479 --> 00:03:17.280
No longer bound by fixed, familiar patterns,

00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:19.960
but pursuing constant variation in shots

00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:21.360
to disrupt the opponent's setup.

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:24.560
No.

00:03:39.319 --> 00:03:40.199
Impossible.

00:03:53.039 --> 00:03:53.439
That's not right.

00:03:53.919 --> 00:03:54.719
There's an extra set of variables.

00:03:54.879 --> 00:03:55.680
The trajectory is off.

00:03:56.199 --> 00:03:56.960
The trajectory is off.

00:03:57.319 --> 00:03:57.960
The trajectory is off.

00:04:08.280 --> 00:04:09.319
That actually went in?

00:04:09.319 --> 00:04:10.199
That's incredible.

00:04:10.199 --> 00:04:10.759
Impossible.

00:04:11.719 --> 00:04:13.120
Math cannot be wrong.

00:04:15.280 --> 00:04:16.800
Perhaps there really is an algorithm

00:04:16.920 --> 00:04:18.480
that can predict every shot.

00:04:18.480 --> 00:04:19.000
Impossible.

00:04:19.079 --> 00:04:20.439
But if everything is calculated,

00:04:21.079 --> 00:04:22.399
what's the fun in playing?

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:24.959
Besides,

00:04:24.959 --> 00:04:26.160
the human factor, the biggest variable,

00:04:26.639 --> 00:04:28.079
cannot be ignored.

00:04:32.920 --> 00:04:33.480
I don't believe it.

00:04:34.160 --> 00:04:35.439
Math is never wrong.

00:04:36.519 --> 00:04:37.079
Impossible.

00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:43.560
Close the betting pool.

00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:45.199
But closing the pool now

00:04:45.439 --> 00:04:46.360
will result in greater losses,

00:04:46.879 --> 00:04:48.240
and we'll face the gamblers' wrath.

00:04:48.319 --> 00:04:49.240
I said close the pool.

00:04:49.240 --> 00:04:49.879
Now.

00:04:57.639 --> 00:04:59.000
You may be the boss,

00:04:59.560 --> 00:05:00.120
but

00:05:00.319 --> 00:05:02.639
your attitude really hurts my feelings.

00:05:03.079 --> 00:05:04.160
How do you know

00:05:04.160 --> 00:05:05.600
that I'm sure to lose?

00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:06.439
After all,

00:05:06.720 --> 00:05:08.439
I'm not playing a match against him.

00:05:08.639 --> 00:05:10.399
I just want him to solve a puzzle.

00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:12.000
The puzzle I set.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:13.240
He definitely can't solve it

00:05:15.959 --> 00:05:16.639
Hei Ba

00:05:17.079 --> 00:05:18.199
What's going on?

00:05:18.720 --> 00:05:20.439
This is the puzzle I've set for you

00:05:20.639 --> 00:05:21.959
Solve it and you win

00:05:22.600 --> 00:05:23.839
Three-Star Pagoda

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:24.439
Right

00:05:24.639 --> 00:05:26.000
It's the Three-Star Pagoda

00:05:26.439 --> 00:05:28.040
Your target ball is the black ball

00:05:28.480 --> 00:05:29.399
You must, without touching

00:05:29.399 --> 00:05:30.759
the red balls,

00:05:30.800 --> 00:05:31.959
hit the black ball

00:05:32.079 --> 00:05:33.199
to solve the puzzle

00:05:33.639 --> 00:05:34.240
I protest

00:05:34.959 --> 00:05:35.839
Kid

00:05:35.839 --> 00:05:37.279
This isn't playing pool at all

00:05:37.879 --> 00:05:38.759
This round is invalid

00:05:39.160 --> 00:05:40.639
It's invalid just because you say so?

00:05:41.079 --> 00:05:42.519
The heiress of Chaoli Group

00:05:42.639 --> 00:05:44.120
wouldn't be so unreasonable, right?

00:05:45.600 --> 00:05:48.000
Xishi, Sister Wu and Ball Boy Wei He are the Puzzle Dragons

00:05:48.319 --> 00:05:50.480
They are experts at designing pool puzzles

00:05:51.160 --> 00:05:52.560
If you can't solve their puzzle

00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:53.959
you can just give up

00:05:54.360 --> 00:05:55.720
Why do you always butt in?

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:57.199
What kind of puzzle is this?

00:05:57.639 --> 00:05:59.360
How can the white ball, without touching

00:05:59.360 --> 00:06:00.879
the other colored balls,

00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:02.199
pocket the black ball?

00:06:02.279 --> 00:06:03.519
That's why it's hard to solve

00:06:04.120 --> 00:06:05.680
That's why it's called a challenge match

00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:07.680
Fail the challenge and you lose

00:06:08.519 --> 00:06:09.160
Hei Ba

00:06:09.759 --> 00:06:11.040
You're not a sore loser, are you?

00:06:11.319 --> 00:06:12.560
How am I supposed to hit this?

00:06:12.879 --> 00:06:13.439
Yeah

00:06:13.439 --> 00:06:15.480
How can the white ball avoid the red ball

00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:16.199
and hit the black ball?

00:06:17.279 --> 00:06:19.439
You can't play jump shots in snooker.

00:06:19.800 --> 00:06:20.199
Right?

00:06:20.399 --> 00:06:21.480
This shot is hard to make.

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:22.680
Hei Ba

00:06:23.399 --> 00:06:25.000
I know you're good at billiards.

00:06:25.279 --> 00:06:26.639
But faced with this puzzle,

00:06:27.319 --> 00:06:28.680
you are also helpless.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:29.800
If you ask me,

00:06:31.040 --> 00:06:32.040
you should just give up.

00:06:36.120 --> 00:06:37.639
Three-Star Pagoda

00:06:40.240 --> 00:06:41.160
You actually know about

00:06:41.160 --> 00:06:42.079
the Three-Star Pagoda.

00:06:42.399 --> 00:06:42.759
Lao Gui

00:06:43.600 --> 00:06:45.199
How do you think this setup can be broken?

00:06:45.480 --> 00:06:47.800
Why are you studying this useless stuff?

00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:51.000
I recently watched a Hong Kong, China TV series.

00:06:51.319 --> 00:06:52.319
It had this kind of setup in it.

00:06:52.800 --> 00:06:53.439
I was curious.

00:06:53.439 --> 00:06:54.240
Wanted to try it myself.

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.319
You know it's a plot from a TV series.

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:58.600
TV series even turn

00:06:58.600 --> 00:07:00.319
matches into martial arts movies.

00:07:00.560 --> 00:07:02.560
Then why don't you go learn martial arts?

00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:04.519
Didn't you tell me

00:07:04.519 --> 00:07:06.199
to create my own moves?

00:07:06.519 --> 00:07:07.920
To create the Seventh Form of Heavenly Craft?

00:07:07.920 --> 00:07:09.279
I have to find inspiration somewhere.

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:14.279
I didn't expect

00:07:14.439 --> 00:07:15.959
that you really brought a TV plot

00:07:15.959 --> 00:07:16.720
into this place.

00:07:16.839 --> 00:07:17.600
What?

00:07:18.319 --> 00:07:19.399
TV series?

00:07:19.759 --> 00:07:20.560
Jiang Nanshuo

00:07:20.759 --> 00:07:22.399
Fictional plots from TV series,

00:07:22.639 --> 00:07:23.519
how can they count?

00:07:23.680 --> 00:07:25.399
It doesn't matter if it's a TV series.

00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:26.879
It's a challenge match.

00:07:27.199 --> 00:07:28.639
You can't just because it's difficult

00:07:29.199 --> 00:07:30.519
cry foul and question it.

00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:31.360
Jiang Nanshuo

00:07:31.399 --> 00:07:33.079
If you can't afford to lose, don't accept the challenge.

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:35.000
Disgracing your Chaoli Group.

00:07:35.279 --> 00:07:35.879
You...

00:07:39.759 --> 00:07:41.360
Who says I can't break this setup?

00:07:43.319 --> 00:07:44.519
Sixth Form of Heavenly Craft.

00:07:45.079 --> 00:07:46.600
Three-Star Pagoda.

00:07:52.600 --> 00:07:53.279
Hei Ba

00:07:53.600 --> 00:07:54.680
You really have confidence

00:07:54.879 --> 00:07:56.279
that you can break this setup.

00:07:56.839 --> 00:07:58.839
You don't really think you have superpowers, do you?

00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:01.160
You've already lost.

00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:02.639
What are you still struggling for?

00:08:02.959 --> 00:08:04.079
Cut the crap.

00:08:05.120 --> 00:08:05.959
Jiang Nanshuo

00:08:06.439 --> 00:08:07.600
Since it's about solving the shot,

00:08:08.240 --> 00:08:10.240
there's no rule saying it must be solved in one stroke, right?

00:08:10.399 --> 00:08:11.399
But we can't let him just

00:08:11.399 --> 00:08:12.480
drag this on indefinitely.

00:08:12.480 --> 00:08:13.720
It won't be indefinite.

00:08:14.680 --> 00:08:16.000
Just need three strokes.

00:08:16.920 --> 00:08:17.240
Good.

00:08:17.800 --> 00:08:18.959
Just a cornered beast fighting.

00:08:19.319 --> 00:08:20.639
I'll give you three chances.

00:08:31.720 --> 00:08:32.639
If you ask me,

00:08:32.799 --> 00:08:33.919
you should just give up.

00:08:34.360 --> 00:08:35.679
No matter how many times, it's useless.

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.279
This is a dead end.

00:08:37.679 --> 00:08:38.879
You can't solve it.

00:08:49.120 --> 00:08:50.840
Can you really solve this ball?

00:08:51.279 --> 00:08:51.759
Yes.

00:08:52.320 --> 00:08:53.600
This time I definitely can.

00:10:08.840 --> 00:10:10.440
Grab Ball Boy Wei He for me.

00:10:10.559 --> 00:10:11.000
Brother Nan

00:10:12.080 --> 00:10:13.200
He's still a child.

00:10:13.480 --> 00:10:14.440
Bring him here.

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:17.000
Don't go over there.

00:10:17.120 --> 00:10:19.399
Back, back, back.

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:20.279
Back.

00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:25.840
Senior Brother

00:10:25.960 --> 00:10:27.799
You actually figured out this move.

00:10:30.440 --> 00:10:31.600
How is Lao Gui's health?

00:10:31.960 --> 00:10:32.679
It's alright.

00:10:32.919 --> 00:10:34.159
Master was worried about you.

00:10:34.600 --> 00:10:35.960
Sent me over to take a look.

00:10:36.200 --> 00:10:36.720
However,

00:10:36.879 --> 00:10:37.720
looking at the situation,

00:10:37.840 --> 00:10:39.279
you should be able to handle it yourself.

00:10:39.600 --> 00:10:41.639
Remember to visit Master when you have time.

00:10:43.039 --> 00:10:43.600
Sis Wu

00:10:43.639 --> 00:10:44.480
Let's go.

00:10:48.120 --> 00:10:49.720
Say hello to Master for me.